cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper is about an indoor positioning system based on WiFi fingerprinting, which is a topic related to networked systems and internet of things. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques for RSS radiomap prediction, which suggests a possible connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper introduces a new propagation model for generating virtual fingerprints, which could be relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper includes experimental results that involve data processing and visualization, which could be related to cs.MM (Multimedia).
